snippet.description:
Sharon Cuneta may be the Megastar, but why do Filipinos love her? I took to the streets to find out the reasons she has captured the hearts of the masses.

Sharon Cuneta, is a multi-awarded Filipino singer, actress and TV host dubbed the Megastar of Philippine Entertainment, and fondly called "Mega" by fans and people from the entertainment industry. Her success in the movies, television and recording make her possibly the greatest Filipino entertainer of all time. Her popularity has translated well into the field of advertising, where she is the highest paid and most effective Filipino celebrity endorser. 

On November 22, 2011, following months of speculations, Sharon's big move to TV5 was made official by signing a staggering 1 Billion contract with the Kapatid Network -- the highest ever paid to a Filipino artist. She parted ways with ABS-CBN, her home network of 24 years, on a cordial note. Her daily afternoon talk show Sharon: Kasama Mo, Kapatid premiered on May 14, 2012 and has been hailed as an engaging program that aims to entertain and to inspire. The show provides the perfect platform for Sharon to be in touch with her audience, reaffirming her stature as a well-loved icon who is now more accessible to fans and viewers alike.

Travis Kraft's official site: http://www.traviskraft.com

snippet.description: After news of his death, there's no shortage of people and celebrities mourning Chokoleit, thanking him mainly for the laughs he gave them. Instagram    When Chokeleit, who passed away aged 46, made an appearance on "It's Showtime" around three months ago, it was one of his quips that drew the loudest laughs from the "madlang pipol."  Joining the show's beauty contest, he introduced himself by saying: "Nang magsabog ang Diyos ng kagandahan, bakit hindi ako inabisuhan? Pero hindi bale, naniniwala naman ako na kapag ang kagandahan ay nakakamatay, tiyak isa ako sa mabubuhay."   It's his bread and butter, this self-deprecating brand of humor. His bent was not to deviate from the norm of how these are delivered, but to mean them in the most brutally honest way possible.  It's what he loves --making people feel good about themselves at the expense, perhaps, of himself. But to describe him as ugly, no matter how often he did this, would be a disservice to the people whose lives he has touched. There's a lot of them.  Genuine is the word that pops up most often when his celebrity friends remember him, most notably when Sharon Cuneta talked about their friendship back in September last year.  "Napaka-tunay na tao --napakabait, napakaganda ng puso. His heart is so beautiful. Matalino siya, masarap kausap, at higit sa lahat talagang kaibigan," Cuneta gushingly shared.   It's also maybe why Vice Ganda, one of the country's comedy icons, is having a difficult time accepting his death, struggling to grasp the reality of losing one of the 'realest' people he knew.  oh my Lord this is really sad. Pls give us strength. — jose marie viceral (@vicegandako) March 9, 2019    When Chokeleit guested on Vice Ganda's late night talk show, he talked about how he never once thought of having plastic surgery. ("Komedyante tayo, hindi sexy star," he said in jest).   And no doubt it was this authenticity that endeared him to many. He will probably be known to most people for his side roles in ABS-CBN movies or for playing the shokoy Pearly in 2004's "Marina," but to those closest to him, it'll be for his genuineness.  He's proudly real --and his jokes are all the more better for it.   View this post on Instagram  A post shared by CHOKOLEIT (@hot_chokoleit) on Jan 14, 2019 at 9:39pm PST

snippet.description:
This shows the Olongapo Firefighters inclination to music and how they are doing a wonderful job failing at it. Pun intended. Jeffrey and Jose are actually good singers and musicians, the rest are what you call "pang-gulo" including me.

For all the gadgets that you see in this video, check out this list of links to own them:
GoPro Hero 4 Session http://amzn.to/2kJa5zy
GoPro Hero 4 Silver http://amzn.to/2kJ2Sjc
Monopod with Tripod Stand: http://amzn.to/2lha0oS
Ipad Mini http://amzn.to/2kJegeL
Acoustic Guitar http://amzn.to/2lh2I4s

All five of the firefighters were invited to a Virginia Beach host family, Olongapenos that have the last name Razon. Yup, they are related to the owners of the Filipino food chain "Razon's." We were invited to swim at their pool which I and Jonathan did. Unfortunately, the swimming pool was freezing and this was early June. I could only do a few laps as the air at the surface of the pool was giving me bronchoconstrictive episodes. I didn't bring my inhaler.

At the first part of the video, you can see us just having fun and playing around. We were recording so everyone was camera shy and doing all sorts of stuff with their voices.

At the second part we were able to do some half successful songs. Michelle's laughing keep throwing us off.

The last song was the only one we ever completed and it was Sharon Cuneta's "Kahit Maputi na Ang Buhok Ko."

Watch more in iWant or TFC.tv 
It was a family affair at the Sharon Cuneta concert in Vancouver, Canada this past week, with her daughter KC Concepcion joining her onstage for a duet of Regina Belle's "If I Could." 
The song, according to Cuneta, holds a special place in her heart as she used to sing it for Concepcion when she was still a child. 
It was the definite highlight of the leg, part of Cuneta's ongoing tour of North America celebrating 40 years of her career. 
Other of her hits she performed included "Mr. DJ" and "Tawag ng Pag-ibig" --one of the first-ever songs she recorded. 
Speaking with Balitang America, Concepcion heaped praise on her mom for the lives she touched throughout her years in the spotlight. 
"Sana maging happy siya palagi and hindi siya makalimutan ng mga Pilipino dahil ang dami na niyang lives na na-touch. She is a true legend," she said. 
Cuneta's tour will take her to Las Vegas, California, and Florida before heading back to Canada for a Toronto stop.

Isang Pamilya Tayo Ngayong Pasko

Nothing is impossible in life as long as we remain as one family in love and in faith.

We Filipinos are known for how deeply we cherish our family and our faith in God. Our family has always been the foundation of our personal values and utmost source of support. Our faith in God is our stronghold and armor against any adversity. This is why despite all the trials we encounter, we remain hopeful and strong.

This Christmas, we are shining the spotlight on individuals, communities and organizations that are examples of determination to succeed and of commitment to improve their lives and the lives of others no matter what the difficulties are.
Our Kapamilya stars and personalities pay tribute and share the stories of these exemplary individuals and organizations that have triumphantly surpassed their challenging situations. These stories of successes have now become sources of inspiration and encouragement to other Filipinos who also dream of changing their lives for the better.
